Cope says the latest developments cast doubt over whether the committee will execute the mandate given to them by Parliament. JOHANNESBURG Congress of the People (Cope) has called on members of Parliament s ad-hoc committee looking into the fitness of the now defunct South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) board to unite and work together.The call comes after the da walked out of Friday's meeting following a disagreement over whether to include recommendations in the committee's draft report.The Democratic Alliance argued for the recommendations to be set out in the document before it is sent to affected parties, but was overruled, which prompted the walk-out.Cope says it is disappointed at the latest developments which cast doubt over whether the ad-hoc committee will execute the mandate given to them by Parliament.Party spokesperson Dennis Bloem said, We are calling upon this party to put their differences aside and put the country first because the SABC must be safe. 